The above list of numbers represents the flowering plants identified and the stars show the months during which they were found to be in flower. The Golf Course was a natural choice for our survey because of its popularity with residents and visitors alike as a pleasant walking area and is used by Newtonmore schoolchildren as part of their playground as well as by golfers. The schoolchildren identified well with this area.
